		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">darryl.revok wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> I feel that Contra has a very arcade-centric difficulty curve. .....<br />If there are any Contra fans out there I'd be curious to hear your thoughts on the game and/or genre.</div><br /><br />I dunno, I thought other than the overly-easy pseudo-3d levels, the difficulty curve was reasonable.  The hangar and the energy zone were significantly more difficult than the jungle and waterfall. The ice field was good middle ground. <br /><br />Really, I think part of the reason the game felt easy is that we played through it a million times with the 30-lives code, until we knew the game backward and forward.  That made it really easy when switching to non-cheating, as we already had figured out the best ways to handle each challenge.<br /><br />(and really, most action games at the time could be mastered in a day or two)

		

